SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 370
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Sonya Ricker for her
twenty-five years of service to Hamblen County.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have evinced an unwavering
commitment to the betterment of their community; and
WHEREAS, Sonya Ricker is one such individual, who has served with distinction in the
Hamblen County Soil Conservation District office for the past twenty-five years, playing an
essential role in supporting the conservation efforts that protect and preserve the land and
natural resources of Hamblen County; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her outstanding tenure and contributions to the Soil
Conservation District, Ms. Ricker was recently honored with a certificate of appreciation from the
Hamblen County Commission, acknowledging her invaluable service to the District, the
residents of Hamblen County, and Tennessee's natural resources; and
WHEREAS, Sonya Ricker's dedication and professionalism have made a lasting impact
on Hamblen County, fostering progress and promoting sustainability through her work with the
Soil Conservation District; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Sonya Ricker for her
twenty-five years of honorable and astute service to the people of Tennessee as a member of
the Hamblen County Soil Conservation District office, extending our best wishes for much
continued success in her future endeavors.
